
[1]banking

   BANK'ING, ppr. Raising a mound or bank; inclosing with a bank. When we
   speak of restraining water, we usually call it banking; when we speak
   of defending the land, we call it imbanking.

   BANK'ING, n. The business or employment of a banker; the business of
   establishing a common fund for lending money, discounting notes,
   issuing bills, receiving deposits, collecting the money on notes
   deposited, negotiating bills of exchange, &c.
